HOUSE BILL 1493
F3 6lr3012
CF SB 574
By: Charles County Delegation
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Charles County – Student Bus Transportation Providers – Provider
3 Displacement
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Charles County Board of Education to provide certain
5 notice and hold a certain public hearing before taking any action that results in a
6 certain displacement of a company that has been providing student bus
7 transportation services in Charles County; and generally relating to student bus
8 transportation services in Charles County.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 7–811
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 7–811.
18 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION, “DISPLACEMENT” MEANS THE PROVISION OF
19 STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES BY THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF
20 EDUCATION IN A MANNER THAT PRECLUDES A COMPANY THAT HAS BEEN
21 PROVIDING THE SERVICES FROM CONTINUING TO PROVIDE THE SERVICES.
22 (2) “DISPLACEMENT” DOES NOT INCLUDE CIRCUMSTANCES IN
23 WHICH:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1493*

2 HOUSE BILL 1493
1 (I) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION DOES NOT
2 RENEW A CONTRACT FOR STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES FOR CAUSE;
3 OR
4 (II) THE COMPANY THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE STUDENT
5 BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES:
6 1. HAS BEEN FOUND TO HAVE ACTED IN A MANNER
7 THREATENING TO PUBLIC HEALTH OR SAFETY;
8 2. HAS BEEN FOUND TO HAVE COMMITTED A MATERIAL
9 BREACH OF A CONTRACT FOR STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES; OR
10 3. REFUSES TO CONTINUE TO PROVIDE STUDENT BUS
11 TRANSPORTATION SERVICES UNDER THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF AN EXISTING
12 AGREEMENT.
13 (B) BEFORE TAKING ANY ACTION THAT RESULTS IN THE DISPLACEMENT OF
14 A COMPANY THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES
15 IN CHARLES COUNTY, THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL:
16 (1) PROVIDE WRITTEN NOTICE OF THE INTENT TO DISPLACE, SENT BY
17 FIRST–CLASS MAIL AT LEAST 45 DAYS BEFORE THE HEARING REQUIRED UNDER
18 ITEM (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, TO EACH COMPANY THAT PROVIDES THE SERVICES
19 IN CHARLES COUNTY; AND
20 (2) (I) CONDUCT A PUBLIC HEARING; AND
21 (II) PROVIDE NOTICE OF THE HEARING TO THE PUBLIC BY
22 PUBLISHING A NOTIFICATION IN A NEWSPAPER OF GENERAL CIRCULATION IN THE
23 COUNTY ONCE EACH WEEK FOR 2 SUCCESSIVE WEEKS BEFORE THE HEARING.
24 (C) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, WITHIN 1
25 YEAR AFTER THE PUBLIC HEARING, AND AT LEAST 2 YEARS BEFORE ANY
26 DISPLACEMENT, THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL PROVIDE
27 WRITTEN NOTICE BY REGISTERED MAIL OF THE DISPLACEMENT TO THE COMPANY
28 PROVIDING THE STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES.
29 (2) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION MAY BEGIN
30 PROVIDING STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES OR CONTRACT WITH
31 ANOTHER COMPANY TO PROVIDE THE SERVICES LESS THAN 2 YEARS AFTER
32 PROVIDING THE NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION IF:

HOUSE BILL 1493 3
1 (I) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION PAYS THE
2 DISPLACED COMPANY THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE SERVICES AN AMOUNT
3 EQUAL TO THE COMPANY’S GROSS RECEIPTS FOR PROVIDING THE SERVICES IN THE
4 COUNTY FOR THE PRECEDING 24–MONTH PERIOD;
5 (II) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION AND THE
6 COMPANY THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE SERVICES AGREE TO A DIFFERENT
7 NOTICE PERIOD OR COMPENSATION AMOUNT; OR
8 (III) THE COMPANY STOPS PROVIDING THE SERVICES IN THE
9 COUNTY.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
11 1, 2026.

